A chief magistrate court in Ondo town, Ondo State, has ordered a 40-year-old farmer, Lomi Adefusi, to cut a thick bush for stealing cocoa beans worth N650 Adefusi was arraigned before the court on a one count charge of stealing. The prosecution told the court that the defendant  stole the farm crop belonging to one Mustapha  Bolarinwa on September 23, 2019. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY Adefusi confessed to stealing the crop and appealed to the court to forgive him. The magistrate, Mrs Odenusi Fadeyi, only ordered Adefusi to cut a thick bush as a punishment and struck out the case.  Man remanded in prison for stealing Bibles, N100,000 Bricklayer dragged to court for allegedly stealing goats Farmers delay Nigeria cocoa shipments over disputed levies